Description: Dr. Reginald Boulos is a Haitian entrepreneur and leader. He is the Chairman of the RB GROUP, a diversified and family owned group of companies operating across several business sectors in Haiti, principally food and general merchandise, car dealership and real estate. The Boulos family is well known in Haiti for its entrepreneurial successes and strong involvement in the field of corporate social responsibility. Dr. Boulos‚Äô family has been in business in the country for several decades, primarily in the commercial, medical and real estate sectors. In 2018, Dr. Boulos launched a new political party named MTVAyiti (Mouvement pour la Transformation et la Valorisation d‚ÄôHaiti) aimed at creating social justice within Haiti composed of four main branches of the population which includes young adults, the Haitian Diaspora, farmers and women. The Third Way movement is a humanist and revolutionary organization with a social-democratic stance. It is a progressive political party, whose aim is to improve the living conditions of Haitian people. It strives to promote private initiative and free enterprise in the market economy, redistribute national wealth fairly through public policies that guarantee the right of all to health, quality and professional university education, equal access to credit in the financial system, and gender equity.
